               <p>I live at <placeName id="t17781209-41-crimeloc251">Enfield-Wash</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17781209-41-crimeloc251" type="placeName" value="Enfield-Wash"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17781209-41-crimeloc251" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17781209-41-off249 t17781209-41-crimeloc251"></join>; I am <rs id="t17781209-41-viclabel252" type="occupation">collector of the toll</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17781209-41-victim498 t17781209-41-viclabel252"></join> at Stamford-Mill . When I came home at night, on Friday was fortnight, I was informed that a place adjoining to my house was broke open, and the fowls gone. I found the boards broke, and the bar partly broke. I lost twelve hens and two cocks. the Prisoner was detected selling the fowls on Friday morning, in Shoreditch. I went there and saw seven of my hens; I know them to be mine; I had kept them five or six years.</p>
               <p>Was this place a shed adjoining to the house? - It does not join to the house; there is a door out of the house into the yard, and then a door into the shed out of the yard.</p>
               <p>Are they all under the same roof? - Yes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17781209-41-person499">
                  SIMON
                   WOODWARD
